Package com.charliai.activities.handlers.web

Class Parse

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.ws.rs.core.Application
      • com.charliai.activities.api.ActivityHandler
        • com.charliai.activities.handlers.web.Parse
  • @Path("/web")
public class Parse
extends ActivityHandler
    The Parse class is part of the CharliAI package for web site traversal and parsing of web pages. The functionality offered in this Class and package is for the purposes of getting direct information for users of the CharliAI application based on their activities (i.e. intents).

        @Path("web_parse")
@POST
@Consumes("application/json")

public javax.ws.rs.core.Response parse​(java.lang.String requestMessage)
        The parse method will obtain a web page using an HTTP GET request and will parse the page in order to obtain relevant details. This method access web page URLs either in a specific web_parse intent or in a search intent. Summary information currently consists of header and paragraph details.
        Parameters:
        requestMessage - String request message
